In Parliamentary debate, the kind we did at Debate Club, there are two team=
s =E2=80=93 the Proposition and the Opposition =E2=80=93 who debate a resol=
ution. The resolution might be something like =E2=80=9CGeneral AI should ha=
ve fundamental rights.=E2=80=9D The Proposition defends the resolution and =
the Opposition tries to poke holes in it.=C2=A0
The two sides go back and forth making arguments, concluding in a rebuttal =
from each team summarizing the debate, reiterating their points, and trying=
 to make clear why their side won. If you want to read the rules, I wrote u=
p a stripped down version for Debate Club [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c=
