KduEpQQvLLaI16oiB28gLWCAuMnNNKW-Xf9BcwtZBc].=C2=A0
There are a few things that you want to do to win a debate.=C2=A0
The most obvious is that you want to find the most and best evidence in fav=
or of your side.=C2=A0
In the course of your research, you will also find evidence that contradict=
s your side. Be aware of this evidence in case you need to defend against i=
t, but by all means, don=E2=80=99t want to bring it up (unless, of course, =
you=E2=80=99re playing an advanced game and want to say things like =E2=80=
=9CI expect that our opponents will tell you that x, y, z=E2=80=A6 they=E2=
=80=99re wrong because a, b, c.=E2=80=9D). Less scrupulous debaters might e=
ven bend or make things up.=C2=A0
Remember, the point in a debate is to win, not to get to the truth.
That=E2=80=99s Debate 101 type stuff. And then there=E2=80=99s the more adv=
anced shit: instead of fighting the battle you were assigned, you start a n=
ew battle about whatever serves your agenda.=C2=A0
